
---

## Step 5: Add, Commit, and Push to GitHub

Run these commands in **PowerShell**:

```bash
cd G:\online-kirana-store

# Add all files
git add .

# Check status (optional)
git status

# Commit with message
git commit -m "Initial commit: KiranaConnect - Complete E-commerce Platform

- User authentication with JWT
- Product management with CRUD
- Shopping cart and wishlist
- Order management with live tracking
- Admin panel and delivery dashboard
- PWA support and email notifications
- UPI QR payment integration"

# Add remote repository (Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your GitHub username)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/kiranaconnect.git

# Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main